{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b64d6952-e346-453a-b13b-8b4cf6948fe4","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n**1. `--filter` → `--treenode-filter`** (MTP's native filter syntax)\n\n**2. Syntax translation:**\n\n| VSTest (`--filter`) | MTP (`--treenode-filter`) |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*` |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` |\n| `&` (AND) | combine in one expression |\n\nYour new command:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n**How it works:**\n- `/**/` — matches any namespace path\n- `*IntegrationTests*` — glob-contains on the test name (replaces `~`)\n- `[Category=Smoke]` — filters on the trait property\n\nSince your project sets `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>`, `dotnet test` delegates to MTP, which uses `--treenode-filter` natively. The old VSTest `--filter` syntax is no longer reliably translated.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cf57a6f7-d7a7-46e0-8fdc-c751be86de19","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is migrating from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3 with MTP (Microsoft Testing Platform). The key differences:\n\n1. With VSTest (v2), the filter syntax was `--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"` which uses VSTest's filter syntax.\n\n2. With MTP (Microsoft Testing Platform), the filter syntax changes. MTP uses `--filter` but the syntax is different from VSTest.\n\nIn MTP, the filter expression syntax uses different operators:\n- `~` (contains) becomes `/` or uses different syntax\n- `&` (and) stays as `&` or uses `and`\n\n\n- Trait filtering works differently with xUnit v3 traits exposed through MTP's filter syntax\n- `FullyQualifiedName` filtering still works but may use treenode syntax as an alternative\n- When `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner` is enabled, `dotnet test` behavior changes with how filters are interpreted\n- MTP uses different operators than VSTest (like `/` for contains instead of `~`) and may require `--treenode-filter` instead of `--filter` for certain scenarios\n- The treenode filter syntax uses glob-like patterns with `[key=value]` for properties, so something like `/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]` would match tests by name and trait\n- When using `dotnet test` with MTP, the `--filter` option gets translated to treenode syntax, where contains patterns become glob wildcards\n- For xUnit v3 specifically, traits map to test properties in the filter expression, and you can either use `--filter` with VSTest syntax (which gets translated) or go directly with `--treenode-filter` for the native MTP format\n\n.","outputTokens":1254,"requestId":"A030:3C520:C6D852:E84208:69FE87A5"},"id":"fda3aec6-77db-428f-9a69-801269997239","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:02:55.770Z","parentId":"fc6e9fa7-0ac7-4db6-b00e-af5dda8a9362"}
